1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:37,162
It was Sianong’s idea to show you this.

3
00:00:37,245 --> 00:00:40,248
That your brother was arrested
in a drug den and buy-bust operation.

4
00:00:40,331 --> 00:00:41,124
Oh, really?

5
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:42,834
-What the heck!
-What do you mean no?!

6
00:00:42,917 --> 00:00:43,960
Stop it!

7
00:00:44,043 --> 00:00:45,462
My brother was arrested.

8
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:54,512
Let’s meet.

9
00:00:54,596 --> 00:00:55,889
I need to talk to you again.

10
00:00:55,972 --> 00:00:57,057
Mikoy…

11
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:58,433
Your brother has been released.

12
00:00:58,516 --> 00:01:01,394
And the police
won’t press charges anymore.

13
00:01:01,478 --> 00:01:02,645
Return the favor, Mikoy.

14
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:03,855
Please help me.

15
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:22,373
Everything must have a contract.

16
00:01:22,457 --> 00:01:24,125
Everything should be documented.

17
00:01:24,834 --> 00:01:27,170
It would be difficult
if we get questioned by the COA.

18
00:01:34,469 --> 00:01:35,678
Oops!

19
00:01:36,262 --> 00:01:37,639
Have you read everything?

20
00:01:37,722 --> 00:01:41,184
And do you understand everything
you read before signing?

21
00:01:41,768 --> 00:01:42,727
Yes.

22
00:01:43,311 --> 00:01:46,064
That I am voluntarily coordinating
with the agency.

23
00:01:46,147 --> 00:01:49,234
Whatever happens to me,
your agency has no liability

24
00:01:49,317 --> 00:01:50,735
and neither does the government.

25
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:53,404
Meaning, dead or alive,

26
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:55,740
you wouldn’t care.

27
00:01:56,282 --> 00:01:58,493
Yup. But to be fair,

28
00:01:58,576 --> 00:02:02,247
you will receive a monthly allowance
for working with us

29
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:04,499
and 13th-month pay as mandated by law.

30
00:02:04,582 --> 00:02:07,794
Plus, 5,000 pesos
for transportation allowance,

31
00:02:07,877 --> 00:02:10,755
and 5,000 pesos for food allowance.

32
00:02:10,839 --> 00:02:13,925
And in case you die in the line of duty,

33
00:02:14,008 --> 00:02:17,303
your family will get
one million pesos and benefits.

34
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:19,222
Wow!

35
00:02:19,305 --> 00:02:21,599
There’s even a bonus if I die.

36
00:02:21,683 --> 00:02:22,517
Nice.

37
00:02:34,904 --> 00:02:36,072
This is fine.

38
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:47,667
Do you know how to use that?

39
00:02:50,378 --> 00:02:51,629
Definitely.

40
00:02:52,338 --> 00:02:53,464
Of course.

41
00:02:56,301 --> 00:02:57,552
What are you doing?!

42
00:02:59,679 --> 00:03:00,805
You could kill someone!

43
00:03:00,889 --> 00:03:02,682
How would I know that was a real gun?

44
00:03:03,975 --> 00:03:04,809
Wait!

45
00:03:07,645 --> 00:03:09,063
Someone might hear us here.

46
00:03:09,147 --> 00:03:11,065
Why are you even giving me that?!

47
00:03:11,149 --> 00:03:12,609
I don't need a gun!

48
00:03:12,692 --> 00:03:14,569
I am not going to kill for you.

49
00:03:14,652 --> 00:03:16,821
Didn't you say I'm just a spy?

50
00:03:20,074 --> 00:03:22,785
You’re right. You don't need a gun.

51
00:03:22,869 --> 00:03:26,706
All you need to do is help us
get information about Viktor.

52
00:03:26,789 --> 00:03:28,750
Buddy, hold this first.

53
00:03:30,752 --> 00:03:31,753
Here.

54
00:03:33,129 --> 00:03:34,172
Open it.

55
00:03:34,964 --> 00:03:36,591
This might be something again.

56
00:03:40,178 --> 00:03:41,512
Oh, wait.

57
00:03:42,347 --> 00:03:43,181
This is mine.

58
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:46,351
Why is it here?

59
00:03:48,394 --> 00:03:49,520
There.

60
00:03:57,028 --> 00:03:58,029
Okay.

61
00:03:58,613 --> 00:04:01,866
This one. You need to find a way

62
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:05,954
to plant this in Donabel
and Viktor Valtrovi's room.

63
00:04:06,037 --> 00:04:07,163
This device…

64
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:11,668
For it to work,

65
00:04:11,751 --> 00:04:12,794
you need to connect it.

66
00:04:12,877 --> 00:04:15,838
When the green light appears,
it means connected.

67
00:04:15,922 --> 00:04:17,882
We will hear you on the other side.

68
00:04:29,686 --> 00:04:32,897
The only problem is,
we don’t have ears inside.

69
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,611
As they say,

70
00:04:39,195 --> 00:04:43,157
the secrets of a family are heard
inside the couple's bedroom.

71
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:48,746
So you need to plant it
inside Donabel and Viktor's room.

72
00:04:57,171 --> 00:04:58,256
Let's go.

73
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,440
Chow.

74
00:05:16,649 --> 00:05:17,650
-Tongits!
-Ah!

75
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:18,735
-Hey.
-Oh my!

76
00:05:18,818 --> 00:05:20,653
Oh my gosh, honey!

77
00:05:29,954 --> 00:05:31,205
Eww!

78
00:05:39,714 --> 00:05:42,216
Yes. Yes, I'm okay.

79
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:44,218
-Hey.
-I'll just go to the restroom.

80
00:05:44,719 --> 00:05:46,679
Can you get us some cake, please?

81
00:05:46,763 --> 00:05:48,723
-Thank you!
-Do you want me to go with you?

82
00:05:49,390 --> 00:05:50,391
No, it's okay.

83
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:11,746
Good day!

84
00:06:23,549 --> 00:06:24,926
Do you think he can do it?

85
00:06:25,009 --> 00:06:27,970
Maybe our new asset is getting cold feet.

86
00:06:31,849 --> 00:06:33,184
I think he'll keep his word.

87
00:06:33,851 --> 00:06:35,269
I hope so.

88
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:40,274
But I'm sensing
that this new asset is a bit scared.

89
00:06:40,358 --> 00:06:42,860
And I think he might
even turn the tables on us later.

90
00:08:44,732 --> 00:08:45,733
There!

91
00:08:45,816 --> 00:08:47,485
-What?
-I'm picking up a signal.

92
00:08:47,568 --> 00:08:48,653
-Wait.
-Is it activated?

93
00:08:48,736 --> 00:08:50,071
-Wait.
-What?

94
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,518
Is it activated?

95
00:09:20,601 --> 00:09:22,270
Not yet.

96
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:24,855
But I really heard a signal earlier.

97
00:09:46,043 --> 00:09:47,295
Hey!

98
00:09:49,630 --> 00:09:50,464
Come in.

99
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:52,508
Come in.

100
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,767
What happened? Did you plant the device?

101
00:10:03,853 --> 00:10:04,770
No.

102
00:10:08,190 --> 00:10:10,484
I knew it. Our asset
is just being a coward!

103
00:10:14,655 --> 00:10:18,326
Because if not, we won't be able
to get any leads.

104
00:10:18,409 --> 00:10:19,243
I know.

105
00:10:19,327 --> 00:10:20,870
But I was thinking

106
00:10:20,953 --> 00:10:24,332
that planting you’re asking me to do
is dangerous.

107
00:10:24,957 --> 00:10:27,084
I'm sure there's a better way than that.

108
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:28,794
Oh, really?

109
00:10:28,878 --> 00:10:30,046
So now,

110
00:10:30,129 --> 00:10:34,050
you're the one who decides
what will happen to our investigation?

111
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:37,428
Just because you've watched
those James Bond movies,

112
00:10:37,511 --> 00:10:38,971
it doesn't mean you know what to do.

113
00:10:39,055 --> 00:10:40,222
You know,

114
00:10:40,306 --> 00:10:42,475
in the short time I got to know Viktor,

115
00:10:42,558 --> 00:10:43,726
he’s really careful.

116
00:10:43,809 --> 00:10:46,312
He even followed me
when I went to the restroom.

117
00:10:46,395 --> 00:10:48,981
If he finds out someone planted
something in his room,

118
00:10:49,065 --> 00:10:51,150
I’m sure I’ll be the first suspect.

119
00:10:51,233 --> 00:10:54,862
And not only that,
our whole operation might be ruined.

120
00:11:00,201 --> 00:11:03,996
I don't know about you, but me,
I don't want to die before my time.

121
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:06,582
Oh! Look at that!

122
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:09,377
Looks like he's even better than us.

123
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:10,294
Why don't you lead instead?

124
00:11:10,378 --> 00:11:11,253
Come on.

125
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:14,924
You know, if you can’t do this,
just tell us.

126
00:11:15,007 --> 00:11:17,343
Or maybe you're just being a coward.

127
00:11:18,803 --> 00:11:21,097
Do you think I'll be insulted by that?

128
00:11:21,180 --> 00:11:25,267
Hey! Anyone you put
in my position would be scared!

129
00:11:25,351 --> 00:11:27,019
Can you two stop?

130
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:29,146
All right, if you don't want to plant it,

131
00:11:29,230 --> 00:11:30,689
what's your alternative?

132
00:11:34,860 --> 00:11:36,070
This is what happened.

133
00:11:55,256 --> 00:11:58,551
You know, it's like a mall.
Like the Mall of Asia.

134
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:54,023
Call me Uncle Vik!

135
00:12:56,942 --> 00:12:59,111
Okay. Uncle Vik!

136
00:13:00,154 --> 00:13:02,364
Oh! You know, if you have a best friend

137
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:03,574
named Uncle Joey,

138
00:13:03,657 --> 00:13:05,075
it would be perfect!

139
00:13:05,826 --> 00:13:09,246
You know, Uncle Vik and Joey…

140
00:13:22,551 --> 00:13:24,803
About what, Uncle Vik?

141
00:13:27,389 --> 00:13:28,933
An opportunity?

142
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:33,646
But the question is,

143
00:13:35,105 --> 00:13:36,732
are you open-minded?

144
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:41,111
And that’s when he offered me
to run Vortex Global Trading.

145
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:44,198
His import-export company based in Manila.

146
00:13:44,865 --> 00:13:46,200
The same Vortex Global Trading

147
00:13:46,283 --> 00:13:49,411
that you said is being used
by the Moraviano Syndicate.

148
00:13:49,995 --> 00:13:54,458
If I agree to it,
we can gather more information

149
00:13:54,542 --> 00:13:56,502
about their illegal operations.

150
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:01,799
Have mercy on me!

151
00:14:07,846 --> 00:14:09,848
You're too noisy. I'm still eating!

152
00:14:10,724 --> 00:14:11,684
Huh!

153
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:13,936
-So what?
-I can't take it anymore.

154
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:14,853
Huh?

155
00:14:14,937 --> 00:14:16,397
-That's enough.
-What?!

156
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:23,320
I guess

157
00:14:23,988 --> 00:14:26,156
this idiot has finally learned.

158
00:14:27,741 --> 00:14:30,244
Let this idiot
be an example to all of you!

159
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:36,458
This is what will happen to you
if you mess

160
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:38,377
with the Moraviano!

161
00:14:51,515 --> 00:14:52,683
Boss, you have a call.

162
00:15:36,310 --> 00:15:37,811
Looks like he has a point.

163
00:15:43,150 --> 00:15:47,529
Well then, welcome back…
to the Philippines.

164
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:16,225
B?

165
00:16:20,854 --> 00:16:23,107
Is there a problem?

166
00:16:26,860 --> 00:16:28,153
Do you want to eat?

167
00:16:29,863 --> 00:16:31,949
Uhm, what's good here?

168
00:16:32,032 --> 00:16:33,659
Lechon? Do you want lechon?

169
00:16:35,786 --> 00:16:38,580
It's really delicious, I promise!

170
00:16:38,664 --> 00:16:39,790
Uh, what else?

171
00:16:39,873 --> 00:16:40,874
Laptinaw.

172
00:16:40,958 --> 00:16:42,543
-Budbod!
-Stop the car!

173
00:16:43,168 --> 00:16:46,463
FOR RENT

174
00:16:46,547 --> 00:16:48,549
-Good morning!
-Good morning.

175
00:16:48,632 --> 00:16:49,550
ID?

176
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:51,885
Four hundred pesos
for the rental and a signature.

177
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:54,221
ID.

178
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:02,646
Keep the change.

179
00:17:02,730 --> 00:17:03,605
Thank you!

180
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:04,648
Okay.

181
00:17:08,027 --> 00:17:09,028
There.

182
00:17:10,404 --> 00:17:11,447
We'll take good care of it.

183
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:13,365
All right, it's safe here with us.

184
00:17:14,283 --> 00:17:15,826
Hey!

185
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:17,703
What are you doing?

186
00:17:17,786 --> 00:17:18,954
What?

187
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:20,831
Are you sure you can handle it?

188
00:17:22,499 --> 00:17:25,544
Are you underestimating my driving skills
because I'm a woman?

189
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:27,379
No.

190
00:17:27,463 --> 00:17:29,339
Of course not. It's just that…

191
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:33,093
You know, maybe you're just not used
to the roads here in the Philippines.

192
00:17:33,594 --> 00:17:36,472
The drivers here
are kind of a bit aggressive.

193
00:17:37,097 --> 00:17:39,016
So they want aggressive?

194
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:02,122
Hold on tight, okay?

195
00:18:04,083 --> 00:18:05,250
Hey!

196
00:19:06,103 --> 00:19:07,563
Nuestra Señora.

197
00:19:10,816 --> 00:19:12,526
This is

198
00:19:13,318 --> 00:19:14,278
Chiara.

199
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:18,365
Hello.

200
00:19:22,452 --> 00:19:23,954
This church

201
00:19:24,746 --> 00:19:26,999
is the center of our lives here.

202
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:29,543
Everyone here

203
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:32,004
gets baptized here,

204
00:19:33,755 --> 00:19:37,759
had the sacrament of confirmation here,
and learned to confess here.

205
00:19:38,886 --> 00:19:41,555
To admit their misdeeds and sins.

206
00:19:45,142 --> 00:19:47,311
Does he have a lot of misdeeds?

207
00:19:47,394 --> 00:19:48,437
Hey!

208
00:19:49,438 --> 00:19:51,607
I could be an awardee
for an exemplary son!

209
00:19:52,482 --> 00:19:53,609
As if.

210
00:19:58,363 --> 00:20:01,283
That's why when the storm hits hard,

211
00:20:02,409 --> 00:20:04,453
when the sea currents are strong,

212
00:20:06,371 --> 00:20:08,123
we all take shelter here

213
00:20:08,624 --> 00:20:10,417
and pray together.

214
00:20:11,418 --> 00:20:15,130
So that Nuestra Señora will protect us.

215
00:20:16,590 --> 00:20:19,760
So throughout your life,
this church will always be there.

216
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:22,846
And when you die,

217
00:20:23,555 --> 00:20:25,641
this is still the last place
you'll pass through.

218
00:20:25,724 --> 00:20:27,851
You will also be blessed here.

219
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:30,646
So, even if this is not as big or as grand

220
00:20:30,729 --> 00:20:33,482
as the churches you have in Europe,

221
00:20:34,274 --> 00:20:36,568
we would never trade it for anything.

222
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:44,618
We really love Nuestra Señora
de Patrocinio de Maria Santisima!

223
00:20:53,001 --> 00:20:53,961
That's why we’re also,

224
00:20:54,753 --> 00:20:55,754
uhm,

225
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:57,589
loved by her.

226
00:20:59,591 --> 00:21:01,260
That's why everyone who falls in love

227
00:21:03,553 --> 00:21:05,264
gets married here.

228
00:21:18,443 --> 00:21:19,778
What about us?

229
00:21:23,615 --> 00:21:25,284
Can we get married?

230
00:21:38,630 --> 00:21:41,258
Michael D. Pinagpala.

231
00:22:30,140 --> 00:22:31,224
Marriage?

232
00:22:33,852 --> 00:22:35,604
You want to get married?

233
00:22:37,272 --> 00:22:38,315
Right away?

234
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:49,910
Oh my.

235
00:22:49,993 --> 00:22:51,286
You men are really something.

236
00:22:51,369 --> 00:22:55,040
Your trigger word is the word "marriage".

237
00:22:57,793 --> 00:22:59,044
No, but it's true.

238
00:23:01,254 --> 00:23:02,380
I want to.

239
00:23:06,802 --> 00:23:08,095
You're right.

240
00:23:09,429 --> 00:23:11,264
Why should I keep beating around the bush?

241
00:23:15,811 --> 00:23:17,187
Chiara, I like you.

242
00:23:23,819 --> 00:23:25,362
Chiara, I love you.

243
00:23:27,322 --> 00:23:29,491
I want to be with you
for the rest of my life.

244
00:23:31,827 --> 00:23:33,286
Chiara, I'm absolutely sure.

245
00:23:35,580 --> 00:23:36,540
Chiara.

246
00:23:47,843 --> 00:23:48,802
Mikoy.

247
00:23:49,302 --> 00:23:50,262
Why?

248
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:53,431
Are you sure?

249
00:23:55,559 --> 00:23:56,852
Look at me.

250
00:24:00,856 --> 00:24:02,274
Look at me.

251
00:24:09,906 --> 00:24:11,324
Ouch!

252
00:24:15,287 --> 00:24:16,121
Why?

253
00:24:16,621 --> 00:24:18,999
You're starting to catch his silliness!

254
00:24:19,082 --> 00:24:21,418
You! You’re the one!

255
00:24:21,501 --> 00:24:22,836
You started it first.

256
00:24:24,212 --> 00:24:25,422
I'm sorry.

257
00:24:27,716 --> 00:24:29,676
-But it's true.
-Stop!

258
00:24:42,397 --> 00:24:43,648
Sorry, Nuestra Señora.

259
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:59,998
Aren’t you used to having
someone next to you in bed?

260
00:25:00,081 --> 00:25:02,417
Me? Hey. Of course!

261
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:03,501
I’ll just freshen up.

262
00:25:06,880 --> 00:25:09,132
Hello, everybody!
We are the parents of Chiara.

263
00:25:09,216 --> 00:25:10,050
Is Mikoy there?

264
00:25:11,384 --> 00:25:13,178
Our asset Mikoy confirmed
that the Valtrovi couple

265
00:25:13,261 --> 00:25:14,888
is here in the Philippines.

266
00:25:16,723 --> 00:25:19,184
I cannot explain what the reason is,

267
00:25:19,267 --> 00:25:22,520
but I’m scared for our son.

268
00:25:23,104 --> 00:25:26,650
You’re doing Chiara a favor
because she grew up with lies.

269
00:25:26,733 --> 00:25:27,943
Chiara?

270
00:25:31,780 --> 00:25:33,156
Mikoy?

271
00:25:35,909 --> 00:25:38,578
And she needs to know the truth
about her family.

272
00:25:57,806 --> 00:25:59,224
Sweetheart!

273
00:25:59,224 --> 00:26:00,224
MkvDrama.net
